        "jsCode": "const config = $('worker config').item.json;\nconsole.log(config);\n\n// Treat null/undefined/empty string as \"no api key\"\nconst validationError = true; // TODO: Code for api validtion error\n\n// If no api key, we should register\nif (validationError) {\n  const registrationData = {\n    workerId: config.serviceId,\n    queueNames: config.queueNames ?? [],\n    maxConcurrentTasks: Number(config.maxConcurrentTasks ?? 1),\n    heartbeatInterval: config.heartbeatInterval, // keep original form if you need it\n  };\n\n  return [\n    {\n      json: {\n        ...config,\n        needsRegistration: true,\n        registrationData,\n      },\n    },\n  ];\n}\n\n// Otherwise, skip registration\nreturn [\n  {\n    json: {\n      ...config,\n      needsRegistration: false,\n    },\n  },\n];\n"
